Claims




How do I submit a claim?




The fastest way to receive benefit payments is to file your claim electronically. Visit Policyholder Services to register or sign in to access your account. You will need your policy number to register.


Was this information helpful?
Yes
No






What information will I need to include with my claim?




Documentation should include the following information:

Provider’s name
Provider’s address and phone number
Policyholder’s Information
Patient Information
Dates of Service
Diagnosis
Specific treatment received from the provider



Was this information helpful?
Yes
No






How do I sign up for Direct Deposit and how long will it take?




Login to Policyholder Services to sign up for direct deposit. Please note, it can take up to two business days to process your request. If you sign up for direct deposit on the same day your claim is submitted, your benefits may be paid by the original payment method.


Was this information helpful?
Yes
No






How do I check the status of my claim?




To check the status of your claim online, login to Policyholder Services or call 800.992.3522 to speak directly to a customer service representative.


Was this information helpful?
Yes
No




One Day Pay




What is ONE DAY PAYSM, and how can I use it?




Many of our claims are processed in just one day. For more information, visit: https://www.aflac.com/onedaypay.


Was this information helpful?
Yes
